> Hi Gang,
>    I know it short notice, but if anyone within a few hundred
>miles of Stockbridge Mass isn't doing anything this coming Sunday (18th)
>Arlo Guthrie is looking for a few buses (and of course drivers) to
>help out with his Walk-a-thon for Huntington's Disease.   Basically we
>need about 8 buses to be parked along the 6 mile route to offer assistance
>if a walker needs it.  Then at the end they will be needed to
>shuttle all the walkers back to the Guthrie Center in Hoosatonic.  The walking
>route is basically Arlo's journey made famous in his song "Alice's
>Restaurant' Starting at the old church, now the Guthrie Center and ending
>at the site of Alice's Restaurant in Stockbridge.  If anyone can help,
>please Call me at work 800-457-1101 ask for Jim in parts.  I'll give
>you Lisa Guthrie's (she's making the arrangements)  phone number to call
>and let her know you'll be coming.  Thanks.
